I think the issue might be more fundamental. Let me think about the problem differently. The actual issue in CODEC-105 might be specifically about the interaction in the single-byte read method. In the `read()` method:

```java
public int read() throws IOException {
    int r = read(singleByte, 0, 1);
    while (r == 0) {  // This causes infinite loop if read(byte[], int, int) keeps returning 0
        r = read(singleByte, 0, 1);
    }
    if (r > 0) {
        return singleByte[0] < 0 ? 256 + singleByte[0] : singleByte[0];
    }
    return -1;
}
```

